import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]
    data['forecastYear'] = data['forecastYear'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='forecastYear', y='value', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of budget forecasts over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Forecast Year')
    plt.ylabel('Budget Forecast Value')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Budget Forecasts', loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['budgetYear'])]
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='value', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['value'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['value'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Budget Forecast Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of budget forecast values?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]
    data['forecastYear'] = data['forecastYear'].dt.year

    avg_values = data.groupby('forecastYear')['value'].mean().reset_index()

    ax = sns.barplot(x='forecastYear', y='value', data=avg_values)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the average budget forecast value for each year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Forecast Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Value')
    plt.legend(title='Average Value', loc='upper left')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
